"{\"uid\": \"komonews.com-news-local-edmonds-post-office-worker-robbed-gunpoint-crime-crisis-washington-seattle-king-county-armed-usps-postal-service-mail-key-mailbox-apartment-public-olympic-view-drive-nissan-zip-codes-mask-puffy-jacket-complexes\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Now  49\\u00b0  Tue  49\\u00b0  Wed  56\\u00b0  byLynnanne Nguyen, KOMO News Reporter  EDMONDS, Wash. -Police are investigating the armed robbery of a postal worker in Edmonds Tuesday night while the worker was working their evening route.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 221, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 58, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOMO-TV\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"KOMO News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOMO-TV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/KOMO-TV\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Edmonds Police Department (EPD) said it happened just before 5:30 p.m. on the 7200 block of 179th St. SW. Surveillance video shows the USPS mail truck going down the street when a black car passes, then blocks the mail truck.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 235, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\", \"score\": 0.9985769160060034, \"rank\": 0.0007896887225119197, \"text\": \"Police Department\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City_Police_Department\"}, {\"begin\": 254, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Environmental_Protection_Department\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"EPD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Environmental_Protection_Department\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Environmental_Protection_Department\"}, {\"begin\": 319, \"end\": 324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/179th_Tunnelling_Company\", \"score\": 0.9997542488212696, \"rank\": 0.00012970437163373015, \"text\": \"179th\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/179th_Tunnelling_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/179th_Tunnelling_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_of_the_compass\", \"score\": 0.9915250344075589, \"rank\": 0.006414678032333715, \"text\": \"SW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_of_the_compass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Points_of_the_compass\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Postal_Service\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USPS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Postal_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Postal_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The armed suspect then gets out and confronts the worker, forcing them at gunpoint to hand over keys for several Edmonds mail routes, including public and apartment mailboxes.\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Police said Edmonds zip codes 98020 and 98026 may be affected.\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He was not injured in any way, there were no shots fired, it was a 'Give me the keys,' he complied and off he went,\\\" EPD Cmdr.\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Josh McClure said.\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"score\": 0.9992813212445808, \"rank\": 0.0007189392095347214, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Lyman\"}, {\"begin\": 827, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"score\": 0.9997806142009165, \"rank\": 0.00021943393934134966, \"text\": \"McClure\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The reality is we want to get the person that's running around putting a gun in people's faces.\\\"\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Just based on the victim's description, it appears he was watching him, waiting for the opportunity to make his move,\\\" McClure added.\", \"from\": 940, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several residences in the area where the incident happened have locked mailboxes because of issues with mail theft in the past, according to neighbors.\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our mailbox was open, and we believe it was stolen out of there, and the police found a car that had stolen mail in it,\\\" Pam Yi, who lives in the area, said of one instance.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1351, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pam_Beesly\", \"score\": 0.9999110224488754, \"rank\": 6.524520057522642e-05, \"text\": \"Pam\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pam_Beesly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pam_Beesly\"}, {\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yi_people\", \"score\": 0.562558545507955, \"rank\": 0.7518732122825924, \"text\": \"Yi\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yi_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yi_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is been mail theft around here for awhile.,\\\" Krista Galloway, who also lives in the area, said.\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1457, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedi